<paragraph blockId="47.[189,1399,442,610]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[189,434,442,468]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,434,442,468]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Ebenacobius atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[446,556,443,469]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished by the combination of appendiculate claws and elytra with distinct but recumbent setae, as long as or shorter than width of interstriae. This species is very close to, if not a synonym of, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[636,749,514,539]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Derelomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turneri" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[636,749,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">E. turneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[758,977,513,539]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see the remarks section under that species). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[298,413,549,574]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis box="[298,413,549,574]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">E. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has short, not or slightly raised squamiform setae on elytra (long, erect and piliform setae in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[285,399,584,609]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Derelomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turneri">
<emphasis box="[285,399,584,609]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">E. turneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
