<paragraph blockId="47.[188,1401,842,1080]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[189,430,842,868]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,430,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Ebenacobius atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[438,545,843,869]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) was described in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" box="[880,1008,842,868]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Derelomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[880,1008,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Derelomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a single male deposited at SAMC (
<bibRefCitation author="Hesse J. C." box="[314,455,878,904]" firstAuthor="Hesse" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the South African Museum" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="475 - 536" part="25" refId="ref30885" refString="Hesse J. C. 1929. Some new species of Curculionidae from South Africa and South West Africa. Annals of the South African Museum 25: 475 - 536." title="Some new species of Curculionidae from South Africa and South West Africa" type="journal article" year="1929">
<collectingRegion box="[314,386,878,904]" country="Germany" name="Hessen" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Hesse</collectingRegion>
1929
</bibRefCitation>
). This specimen was loaned to Guillermo Kuschel (loan 24018) who undertook a study on palaeotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1865" box="[467,601,913,939]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Derelomini">Derelomini</taxonomicName>
from 2007. Unfortunately he passed away before he could complete this work and left the very preliminary manuscript and the material borrowed from institutions was partly not recovered (see postscript in 
<bibRefCitation author="Haran J. &amp; Beaudoin-Ollivier L. &amp; Benoit L. &amp; Kuschel G." box="[653,869,983,1010]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Haran" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 32" part="684" refId="ref30703" refString="Haran J., Beaudoin-Ollivier L., Benoit L. &amp; Kuschel G. 2020. Revision of the palm-pollinating weevil genus Elaeidobius Kuschel, 1952 (Curculionidae, Curculioninae, Derelomini) with descriptions of two new species. European Journal of Taxonomy 684: 1 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2020.684" title="Revision of the palm-pollinating weevil genus Elaeidobius Kuschel, 1952 (Curculionidae, Curculioninae, Derelomini) with descriptions of two new species" type="journal article" year="2020">
Haran 
<emphasis box="[737,798,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). Despite intensive search in the material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1865" box="[191,325,1018,1044]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Derelomini">Derelomini</taxonomicName>
loaned, the 
<typeStatus box="[471,574,1018,1044]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species could not be identified and is provisionally considered as lost.
</paragraph>
